  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🛠️ Design Compliance RAG System\n",
    "### *AMD Hackathon Implementation*\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook implements a high-performance Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system for design compliance. It leverages **ChromaDB** for vector storage and **Ollama** for local LLM inference.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Improvements from `x.md`:**\n",
    "- ✅ Automated collection name detection (Fixed: `design_guides` vs `regulations`)\n",
    "- ✅ Optimized for available model (`qwen3:4b`)\n",
    "- ✅ Premium Interactive UI with `ipywidgets`\n",
    "- ✅ Rich formatting for citations and sources\n",
    "- ✅ Improved Error Handling for database and Ollama connectivity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup & Configuration\n",
    "Initializing dependencies and locating the vector database."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import chromadb\n",
    "import ollama\n",
    "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n",
    "from IPython.display import display, Markdown, HTML\n",
    "import ipywidgets as widgets\n",
    "from IPython.display import clear_output\n",
    "\n",
    "# Config\n",
    "CHROMA_PATH = \"../chroma_db\"\n",
    "COLLECTION_NAME = \"design_guides\"  # Validated from local storage\n",
    "EMBEDDING_MODEL = \"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\"\n",
    "OLLAMA_MODEL = \"qwen3:4b\"           # Validated from ollama list\n",
    "TOP_K = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Setup complete.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Model & DB Initialization\n",
    "Connecting to the existing index and loading the embedding model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize Embedding Model\n",
    "print(f\"🔹 Loading embedding model: {EMBEDDING_MODEL}...\")\n",
    "embedding_engine = SentenceTransformer(EMBEDDING_MODEL)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Connect to ChromaDB\n",
    "print(f\"🔹 Connecting to ChromaDB at {CHROMA_PATH}...\")\n",
    "client = chromadb.PersistentClient(path=CHROMA_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    collection = client.get_collection(COLLECTION_NAME)\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ Connected! Collection '{COLLECTION_NAME}' contains {collection.count()} chunks.\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"❌ Fatal Error: {e}\")\n",
    "    print(\"HINT: Check if chroma_db directory is correctly placed.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Core Logic\n",
    "Functions for retrieval, prompt construction, and generation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def retrieve_context(question, top_k=TOP_K):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Retrieves relevant chunks from ChromaDB.\"\"\"\n",
    "    query_embedding = embedding_engine.encode(question).tolist()\n",
    "    results = collection.query(\n",
    "        query_embeddings=[query_embedding],\n",
    "        n_results=top_k\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return results[\"documents\"][0], results[\"metadatas\"][0]\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_prompt(question, chunks):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Constructs the compliance-focused prompt.\"\"\"\n",
    "    context = \"\\n\\n\".join(chunks)\n",
    "    return f\"\"\"\n",
    "You are a design compliance expert for AMD projects.\n",
    "Use ONLY the provided context to answer the question below.\n",
    "If the answer is NOT in the context, explicitly state: \"Insufficient information found in regulations.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "CONTEXT FROM GUIDELINES:\n",
    "{context}\n",
    "\n",
    "QUESTION:\n",
    "{question}\n",
    "\n",
    "RESPONSE FORMAT:\n",
    "1. Direct Compliance Answer\n",
    "2. Technical Justification\n",
    "3. Reference/Metadata ID\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def generate_answer(prompt):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Generates response using local Ollama model.\"\"\"\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        response = ollama.chat(\n",
    "            model=OLLAMA_MODEL,\n",
    "            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        return response[\"message\"][\"content\"]\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        return f\"⚠️ Error contacting Ollama: {e}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def ask_compliance_rag(question):\n",
    "    \"\"\"End-to-end pipeline with rich visual output.\"\"\"\n",
    "    chunks, metadata = retrieve_context(question)\n",
    "    prompt = build_prompt(question, chunks)\n",
    "    answer = generate_answer(prompt)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Render Output\n",
    "    display(Markdown(f\"## 🤖 Assistant Response\"))\n",
    "    display(Markdown(answer))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    display(HTML(\"<br><div style='border-top: 2px solid #555; padding-top: 10px;'><h4>📚 Evidence & Citations</h4></div>\"))\n",
    "    for i, (chunk, meta) in enumerate(zip(chunks, metadata), 1):\n",
    "        with display(HTML(f\"<div style='background: #f4f4f4; padding: 10px; margin: 5px; border-radius: 5px; color: #333'><b>Source {i}</b> | ID: {meta.get('id', 'N/A')}<br><small>{chunk[:500]}...</small></div>\")):\n",
    "            pass"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. 🎮 Interactive Assistant\n",
    "Run this cell to start chatting with the Design Compliance Database."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# UI Components\n",
    "input_text = widgets.Textarea(\n",
    "    placeholder='e.g., What are the accessibility requirements for dark mode?',\n",
    "    description='Question:',\n",
    "    layout={'width': '100%', 'height': '80px'}\n")\n",
    "button = widgets.Button(\n",
    "    description=\"Analyze Context\",\n",
    "    button_style='primary',\n",
    "    layout={'width': 'max-content', 'margin': '10px 0'}\n",
    ")\n",
    "output_area = widgets.Output()\n",
    "\n",
    "def on_click(b):\n",
    "    with output_area:\n",
    "        clear_output()\n",
    "        if input_text.value.strip():\n",
    "            print(\"🔍 Searching knowledge base...\")\n",
    "            ask_compliance_rag(input_text.value)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            print(\"⚠️ Please enter a question.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "button.on_click(on_click)\n",
    "\n",
    "display(Markdown(\"--- \"))\n",
    "display(input_text, button, output_area)"
   ]
  }
 ],
